Ice out May 15.  Spring water level is the highest it has been for 14 years and is about normal.  Brush and trees that have taken over the expanded shoreline are now standing in water.  Exposed lake bottom which in some locations were  50 to 75 yards wide are again covered with water.

Has gotten dry with only big downpours once in awhile.  The lake has gone up as much as an inch and a half during these events  but returns to the starting level within a few days. column2: weather has cooled- little boating activity
continues to be cool weather wise
Aug temps 3 degrees below average- lake activity has been very quiet-
weather is very nice with warm temps and sunny days
temps above average- has been one great Sept
precipitation has been low- September should have been August

ice out out may 6- latest known date may 8 late 50's.  30" of ice during winter- 99.9" of snow.  water level slightly higher than last year at ice out.  lots of trees showing stress from standing in water last year.  a fringe of dead brush rings the shore line in some places 50 yds wide.  water is standing in places that I've never seen.  there has been a red tint to the surface water which settles to the bottom in calm water conditions and covers the sand making it look rusty

water has a fair amount of floating debris due to the high water and windy conditions  the past two weeks- along most of the shore line there is no beach for the debris to be deposited on so it continues to be pushed  around by the wind.
lake level has come back up after dropping due to lack of precipitation

8+ inches of precipitation second week of June-  4.6" in four hours- 1.6" in 20 min.  reports of 10" within a half mile of this location.  lake went up 4.5" additional rise in the lake level- docks under water and floating away- boat lifts have had to be relocated.

lots of activity on the lake with the summer in full swing.  a group of 15 loons were on the lake during the week of the fourth.  daughter got a great video while kayaking early one morning- the loons danced and put on a real show  lots of activity on the lake with the summer in full swing.  a group of 15 loons were on the lake during the week of the fourth.  daughter got a great video while kayaking early one morning- the loons danced and put on a real show
people activity has shown a decline ( school sports have started)

precipitation has gotten spotty and somewhat below average.  the 80's and 90's of June have cooled- nights cooled into the 50's  the lake has not warmed up as in the past- a 20 degree drop between 15' and 25' and the difference between May 13 (42 degrees at 32 feet ) and July 24 (50 degrees at 32 feet)  was only 8 degrees of temp change.

lake has dropped 6" from ice out- precip. has been spotty and heat continues in the 80's and 90's. tree loss continues along the shoreline and in some cases deep into the woods.  one area if 100 year old pines is standing a foot or more deep in water for the second year.  good crop of LPB in lower lake while other water plants are dying.
still a fair amount of pontoon activity and an unusual numbers of people around and about
ice out Apr 29- 2019; today May 6 is fishing season opener;  a few boats out but very little action reported;  been cold with rain; water is higher than last spring
water is high and trees and brush that are dead are more evident some are 50 yards from the current shore line
there was a report of loons nesting in one of the partly submerged trees along the east shore- some 25 yards from shore
the loon nest has not survived- 4" of rain has raised the water and flooded the nest and strong winds washed it away- the adults are around but do not appear too interested in a do over;

the lake is mostly unused except for a few fisher persons; schools in a lot of cases are still in session and after last winter will continue for awhile longer; seems to be only a few ducks around and few small birds

there have been a few people at their places and most water equipment is out; generally dock services are way behind due for the need to adjust docks and lifts for the high water conditions; several wood dock sections have drifted by that were set in the lake before the water came up during the heavy rains

lake has come up 6" after ice out all in  precipitation;  water is 12" or more higher than any time in 65 years; there is no beach so the water is up against the hill part of the banks and can't spread out so it just gets higher
the lake is busy with the fourth of July people; boat traffic is high
very few people up at their places after being here for a week or two for the fourth; very quiet

water has gone down 3.5" to 4" in past month; very little precipitation in July- 2.5" in the rain gauge; activity on the lake has been very low even on weekends; more fisher persons than skiers;  beach is starting to show water has gone down 3.5" to 4" in past month; very little precipitation in July- 2.5" in the rain gauge; activity on the lake has been very low even on weekends; more fisher persons than skiers;  beach is starting to show water has gone down 3.5" to 4" in past month; very little precipitation in July- 2.5" in the rain gauge; activity on the lake has been very low even on weekends; more fisher persons than skiers;  beach is starting to show; water temp is colder than usual particularly from 20' down

things have started to wind down with start of sports practice for schools;  weather has been cooler than normal by 5 to 8 degrees   things have started to wind down with start of sports practice for schools;  weather has been cooler than normal by 5 to 8 degrees
air temps have been 5-8 degrees below average' windy- cloudy days- temps low 40's to mid 60's;  lake has cooled off faster than usual
summer has ended;  most water stuff has been removed and some places are closed up;

a number of people have commented about the absence of crows;  there are none flying and making fall noises;  road kills are only visited by ravens and eagles; blue jays are not picking up acorns and making their usual fall noises; black birds  are not flocking up and robins are few and far between; strange fall a number of people have commented about the absence of crows;  there are none flying and making fall noises;  road kills are only visited by ravens and eagles; blue jays are not picking up acorns and making their usual fall noises; black birds  are not flocking up and robins are few and far between; strange fall
ice out Apr 18- cool spring ice just melted away with no wind to push it around
weather stays cool- spring is slow
cool most of June- temps averaged 5 to 7 degrees below average
cool most of June- temps 5 to 7 degrees below average
very busy 4th-  lots of boats- two surf boats making big waves almost every day
above average rainfall-  two rain sessions of over two inches-  water temp during the 4th near 80 degrees depending on location-  rains caused water temp to drop rapidly during the next two weeks
still lots of activity on the lake-  school start is in question so no reason to go home

below average rain has caused the water to drop 3 to 4 inches-  heavy boat use during the first two weeks of Aug.   surf boats creating destructive wave action on some shore locations-  way more people here all summer than on an average year- cottages with several weeks of use during the summer have been in constant use with groups of people       below average rain has caused the water to drop 3 to 4 inches-  heavy boat use during the first two weeks of Aug.   surf boats creating destructive wave action on some shore locations-  way more people here all summer than on an average year- cottages with several weeks of use during the summer have been in constant use with groups of people
